## Adding a New Meeting

1. Create a new folder: `app/meetings/COURSE-DD-MONTH-YYYY/`
2. Copy `app/meetings/cheltenham-13-march-2026/page.tsx` into it
3. Update the `RACES` array at the top with the new meeting's data
4. Add the meeting to `app/archive/page.tsx` (MEETINGS array at top)
5. Commit and push to GitHub — Vercel deploys automatically in ~60 seconds

### Free vs Paid rule
- First race in every meeting: set `free: true`
- All other races: set `free: false`
- Users with an active subscription or valid day pass see everything

---

## Clerk Setup

In your Clerk dashboard, make sure:
- Allowed redirect URLs include `https://pacemap.co.uk`
- Sign-in URL: `/sign-in`
- Sign-up URL: `/sign-up`
- After sign-in redirect: `/`
- After sign-up redirect: `/`

---

## Local Development

```bash
npm install
# Create .env.local with all environment variables above
npm run dev
# Site at http://localhost:3000
```
